cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new sequence alignment algorithm that improves classification accuracy and is more robust and scalable than existing methods. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to machine learning, computer vision, artificial intelligence, data structures, and neural networks. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the problem of sequence learning and alignment. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories as they are relevant to the algorithmic and computational aspects of the proposed method.
